Additional details

This pre-owned or refurbished product has been professionally inspected and tested to work and look like new. How a product becomes part of Amazon Renewed, your destination for pre-owned, refurbished products: A customer buys a new product and returns it or trades it in for a newer or different model. That product is inspected and tested to work and look like new by Amazon-qualified suppliers. Then, the product is sold as an Amazon Renewed product on Amazon. If not satisfied with the purchase, renewed products are eligible for replacement or refund under the Amazon Renewed Guarantee.

These products are backed by the Amazon Renewed Guarantee. Pre-owned Certified is part of the Climate Pledge Friendly program that helps you discover and shop for more-sustainable products.

What is Amazon Renewed?
Amazon Renewed is your trusted destination for products that are inspected, tested, and refurbished as necessary to be fully functional.
Quality you can afford
Amazon Renewed products offer an affordable option so you can save on the brands you love.
Products you can trust
All products have been professionally inspected, tested, cleaned, and refurbished as necessary by Amazon-qualified suppliers.
Purchases with an impact
Your Amazon Renewed purchase extends the lifetime of this product and reduces electronic waste.
Trusted coverage
Your purchase is eligible for Amazon Renewed coverage in conjunction with Amazon's Return Policy and the A-to-z Guarantee.
What should I expect to receive with my Amazon Renewed purchase?
All Amazon Renewed purchases will come with accessories equivalent to those that shipped in the box when new. These items may not be original but will be compatible and fully functional. Amazon Renewed products will be packaged in either original packaging or in a new and clean cardboard box.
In what condition can I expect my Amazon Renewed product to be?
Product will be restored to its original factory settings and will be in one of the following cosmetic conditions Premium, Excellent, Good or Acceptable. Learn more

    • Mary B.
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Amazing Watch! No longer worried about battery.
      Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2025
      Size: 46 mmColor: black
      My biggest concern when buying this watch was battery life. When it came initially, I put it on the charger for over an hour, but still had no sign of it charging. I was worried I got a defective watch or charger. I called support, and they were very kind, and said to let... See more
      My biggest concern when buying this watch was battery life. When it came initially, I put it on the charger for over an hour, but still had no sign of it charging. I was worried I got a defective watch or charger. I called support, and they were very kind, and said to let it charge for another hour, and then to call again if it still showed no sign. 2 HOURS later, I picked up my phone to call again, and right at that moment it turned on. It only showed 2% on the charge, but I was really happy to see it working. It took a while to reach a decent charge, about 50%, but then I took it off and got to work setting it up.

      Updates took a while, and even at one point it told me a few times it couldn't update for whatever reason. Past that, I've had no issue. After about an hour it had drained over 40%, and my concerns over battery life started to become true. I set the display to be the lowest it could be, I turned off location, and turned off the feature that automatically wakes up my watch screen. Still didn't help.

      BUT, once all the updates were done and day 2 came around, it had amazing battery life. I put it on the charger in the mornings when I shower and get ready for the day, about an hour, and it's fully charged after that. Even as of now, sitting here writing this review, about 36 hours since the last charge, I've just passed 40% battery.

      I will admit, I don't use a lot of apps. I bought this for the silent alarms and health monitoring, so lets talk about that. It easily detects when I start walking long distances, so I don't have to search for that function. The last two days it's been giving me reminders to start moving again after sitting for too long. I don't know where to turn it off (I've looked) but it's grown on me and I like it. This watch has better sleep tracking than my last, and its been very helpful to me. Vibrations are really strong, which I really like for silent notifications and alarms... I am a heavy sleeper though, so I have yet to wake up to any of these alarms without the sound. I really like the rotating bezel, but I'm afraid its been the culprit of accidently dismissing and snoozing alarms. It's not my only alarm source, but I kind of wish it was, to avoid waking roommates.

      It's been great at tracking heart rates, also something essential for me. I set it to track it all the time, because every 10 minutes would often miss the times I felt my heartrate skyrocket. It's had no impact on the battery, which I think is great.

      I have a rather small wrist, so maybe I should have gotten a smaller watch, but I do like the fit regardless. The band that comes with it makes it kind of uncomfortable, and I constantly have a weird gap because of how stiff the band is. It's gotten better the more I've worn it, but its still there after about a week, so I'm planning on buying another. It's really lightweight, haven't ever felt like it was too heavy. I got a simple black model, which I really appreciate since I work on concert venues quite often, and black attire is normal for me.

      All in all, I really love this watch, and would definitely recommend to anyone. If you plan on using the watch for the apps, I think another watch would be better for the batter life, but for my use it's been perfect.
      10 people found this helpful

      Out of the box, there were a LOT of updates, as expected.

      What I like:
      Lot's of app options. I use activity tracker, nutrition, reminders, alarms, text, phone and some media.

      Fit is good, stays in place on wrist with little movement. Felt a bit heavy at first, but I became accustomed within 2-3 days. Now I don't notice it.

      Plenty of customizable watch faces. Easy to understand and install.

      Screen clarity is very good.

      Touch screen is also customizable, I was able to adjust presets to better suit my use.

      FYI - Watch will not charge on older power blocks. Make sure your blocks are 2.0.

      What I disliked:
      Battery life is the only serious disappointment. For a watch that recommends wearing at night, I would expect 48 - 72 hr batt life, mine gets approx 24 hrs.

      Yesterday I received the Samsung Watch 4 -10/2024. I bought it used and it came as expected a few micro scratches nothing important. I paid about $90 dollars for it. The watch came with 66% of the battery and after setting it up (which was easy) I can say I was impressed... See more
      Yesterday I received the Samsung Watch 4 -10/2024. I bought it used and it came as expected a few micro scratches nothing important. I paid about $90 dollars for it. The watch came with 66% of the battery and after setting it up (which was easy) I can say I was impressed by the amount of things the watch can do. However, that's as far as it goes right to this point. I charged the watch, after setting it up, to 99% battery. I went to bed wearing it to check the sleep monitor at work. It did work as expected. I slept for about 5-6 hours and watch was at about 40% battery. I did not like that at all. It let me know that in full use I probably will not make it through the entire day. I will update on that today because I got full day of work plus gym workout. A serious, and why the 3 stars, is because Samsung failed to alert people (its watch customers at least) that without a Samsung phone you can not use about 40% of the advertised features in this watch, which as I said before there are lots of them. I have a Motorola Razr 2023 and I can not install the Samsung Health Monitoring app on my phone because it is not a Samsung phone (something that it would have giving me paused to buy it). The Samsung Health Monitoring is preinstalled in the watch but it will not work if not installed on your phone. There are some features that still can be used through the SAMSUNG HEALTH app (not to be confused with the monitoring app which measures blood pressure, glucose and the works). You can install Google Fit which is nice for me since I use it for workouts. I have a Samsung tablet which I use for work, but there you can not install the SHM app either, it is only allowed to be installed in phones. I will give an update in couple of weeks. Update 4 days after purchase. After wearing the watch for couple of days I increased my rating to 4 stars. The amount of customization in this watch is impressive. Connectivity is strong it won't disconnect from my phone easily (one of the problems I have with the Tic Watch that kept disconnecting from my phone and it was a pain in the back while running because I couldn't manage the music) in the Samsung watch it's not happening. Battery life is not the best but with some tweaking at night it can be manageable. Eating only 15 to 20% through the night. Changing take 2 hours from single digit to above 90%. So far I'm happy with the purchase. About the health monitor which is one of my major gripes with Samsung, I spoke to few people that have the entire Samsung platform and the average answer was that health monitor didn't work as good or as expected. Wearing the watch at full power at work and gym, usually 10 to 12 hrs, the watch consumes about 50 to 70% of the battery. So charging it every day is a must. Keep this in mind when buying it. It works for me because I can manage to charge twice a day for about 1 hr. I will update again in a month or so.
